12/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- The fire that erupted in part of the Kirkuk-Ceyhan oil pipeline after a deadly explosion has been contained, authorities announced on Wednesday (August 11th). 
Two people were killed in Tuesday's blast, believed triggered by members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK). 
A third passerby was injured. 
Several firefighting teams joined efforts to extinguish the blaze, which forced authorities to temporarily stop the flow of oil through the pipeline. 
(MIA, Press TV, Hurriyet - 11/08/10)
